<msubsup><mrow/><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow><mn>1</mn></msubsup><mtext>n</mtext>

<mo>+</mo>

<msubsup><mrow/><mn>+1</mn><mrow><mspace width="0.5em"/><mn>0</mn></mrow></msubsup><mtext>e</mtext>

<mo>;</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> (c) In a proton-rich nucleus, an inner atomic electron can be absorbed. In simplest form, this changes a proton into a neutron: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow>

<msubsup><mrow/><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>1</mn></msubsup><mtext>p</mtext>

